I just stuck this in my PS1:<p><pre><code>    hr() {
        printf &#x27;=%.0s&#x27; $(seq $((${COLUMNS} - 20)))
    }

    PS1=&quot;${GREY}\d ${RED}\$(hr)${GREY} \t&quot;
</code></pre>
It dynamically adjusts to the width of the terminal, and looks like this:<p><pre><code>    Mon Feb 10 ======================================== 16:30:30
</code></pre>
My complete BASH prompt: <a href="https://bitbucket.org/wyatt/dotfiles/src/25cb260a05b68dd81a5c8710b5034a0b08ea9a81/bashrc?at=default#cl-47" rel="nofollow">https://bitbucket.org/wyatt/dotfiles/src/25cb260a05b68dd81a5...</a>
